# 🧱 TECH STACK DOCUMENT

## Product: Personal Portfolio Website

## Framework: Next.js (App Router)

## Version: 1.0

---

# 1️⃣ Architecture Overview

## Architecture Type:

* **Frontend-first application**
* Static + partially dynamic
* Server Components by default (Next.js App Router)

## Rendering Strategy:

* Static Site Generation (SSG) for pages
* Optional Server Actions for contact form

Why?

* Portfolio doesn’t change often
* Faster performance
* Better SEO
* Cheaper hosting

---

# 2️⃣ Core Framework

## 🚀 Next.js

* Version: Latest stable (14+)
* Routing: App Router
* File-based routing
* Built-in SEO support
* Image optimization
* Server + Client components

Why Next.js?

* You already use it
* Production-ready
* SEO-friendly
* Easy deployment on Vercel

---

# 3️⃣ Language

## 🟦 TypeScript

Why?

* Strong typing
* Better developer experience
* Prevents bugs early
* Makes your portfolio look professional

---

# 4️⃣ Styling System

## 🎨 Tailwind CSS

Why?

* Fast UI development
* Utility-first
* Easy dark mode support
* Clean design control

Dark Mode Strategy:

* class-based strategy
* Controlled via ThemeToggle component
* Uses localStorage to persist theme

---

# 5️⃣ UI Components Strategy

Option A (Recommended):

* Custom components (clean and minimal)

Option B:

* shadcn/ui (if you want polished components)

For a portfolio:
Keep it lightweight and custom.

---

# 6️⃣ Animations

## ✨ Framer Motion (Optional but Recommended)

Use for:

* Fade-in sections
* Hover effects
* Smooth transitions

Why?

* Modern feel
* Lightweight
* Works perfectly with Next.js

---

# 7️⃣ Icons

## 🖼️ Lucide React

Why?

* Clean modern icons
* Tree-shakeable
* TypeScript friendly

---

# 8️⃣ Fonts

## 📝 next/font (Built-in)

Use:

* Inter or Poppins

Why?

* Automatic optimization
* No external request
* Better performance

---

# 9️⃣ Images

Use:

* Next.js Image Component

Benefits:

* Automatic resizing
* Lazy loading
* Optimization

---

# 🔟 State Management

Minimal state required.

Use:

* React useState
* Context API (only for theme if needed)

No need for Redux / Zustand.

